definitions.definition: To move or pass from one place, person or thing to another.
examples: to transfer the laws of one country to another; to transfer suspicion

definitions.definition: To convey the impression of (something) from one surface to another.
examples: to transfer drawings or engravings to a lithographic stone

definitions.definition: To exit one mass transit vehicle and board another (typically one belonging to a different line or mode of transportation) to continue a journey .
To arrange for something to belong to or be officially controlled by somebody else.
examples: The title to land is transferred by deed.

definitions.definition: To move from a wheelchair to another seating surface, or to a wheelchair from another seating surface.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To move or pass from one place, person or thing to another.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To convey the impression of (something) from one surface to another.
( transport , of a traveler ) To exit one mass transit vehicle and board another (typically one belonging to a different line or mode of transportation) to continue a journey .
( intransitive ) To be or become transferred.
( transitive , law ) To arrange for something to belong to or be officially controlled by somebody else.
( intransitive ) To move from a wheelchair to another seating surface, or to a wheelchair from another seating surface.
